public Counterexample check(IGraph<T> sourceGraph,
                            ITemporalInvariant invariant)
                     throws ParseErrorException
Checks the formula after pre-processing it. So it's allowed to have things in it like WFAIR(a).

Parameters:
sourceGraph - The expression to check (it has to be evaluated before!)
invariant - the formula to check
Returns:
a counter example, or null if the formula is satisfied
